# Local development changes :
    In Client side:
    clien/src/api/index.js file change the url 
    const url = 'http://localhost:5000/posts';  //for local dev testing
    
    In Server side:
        in .env file add PORT=5000

# Production related changes :
    In Client side:
    clien/src/api/index.js file change the url 
    const url = 'http://localhost:5000/posts';  //for local dev testing
    
    In Server side:
        in .env file add PORT=5000


# Deployment Process:
    Client : 
        - build the front end client folder with 'npm run build' command
        - deploy build file at netlify.com
        - can change the domain name in the domain settings

    Server:
        - remove the PORT = 5000 line in the .env file
        - add a .gitignore and add node_module to it
        - follow the process given here:  https://dashboard.heroku.com/apps/memoriesapp001/deploy/heroku-git
